      <body>
         
            
               <p>Roberts (he often spelled it 'Robarts') was a native of
                     <placeName>Cornwall</placeName> who became a <seg ana="itinerancy">traveling
                     preacher</seg> in <date when="1750">1750</date>. He left the <seg ana="itinerancy">itinerancy</seg> after a few years, settling into a career in
                  business in <placeName>Tiverton</placeName>, where he supported the Methodist work
                  in this capacity. See Atmore, <hi rend="italic">Memorial</hi>, 346–56; and Pawson,
                     <hi rend="italic">Letters</hi>, 3:144.</p>
            
         
